<span id="freeTextContainer17989147119545805340">I can&apos;t recommend this highly enough. This is not an anti-religion screed at all, but comes at the topic of religion as a naturally emerging aspect of humanity in a thoughtful, funny, accessible way. It is &quot;New Atheist&quot; only in that it calls for open questioning and research of religion and its utility (and it&apos;s written by an atheist). </span>
  <span id="freeText17989147119545805340" style="display:none">I can't recommend this highly enough. This is not an anti-religion screed at all, but comes at the topic of religion as a naturally emerging aspect of humanity in a thoughtful, funny, accessible way. It is "New Atheist" only in that it calls for open questioning and research of religion and its utility (and it's written by an atheist). </span>
